title: Must Watch: Is this the World’s Highest North Shore feature?
content:
Marcin “Banan” Matuszny and co may have built and ridden the World’s Highest North Shore feature. Though it’s not the skinniest skinny you’ve ever seen, it is jaw-droppingly high. The consequences of overbalancing don’t bear thinking about. Marcin claims this skinny stands at 13 metres high above the creek as it winds throughout the conifers.

The post Must Watch: Is this the World’s Highest North Shore feature? appeared first on Bikerumor.
author: Jessie-May Morgan
